bsite=The Straits Times |access-date=5 July 2019 |date=30 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===July===\n* 1 July \u2013 A cycling network is launched in [[Jurong]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/cycling-path-network-that-connects-jurong-east-chinese-garden-and-lakeside-unveiled|title=Cycling path network that connects Jurong East, Chinese Garden and Lakeside unveiled|date=2017-07-01|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref>\n* 3 July \u2013 [[Prime Minister of Singapore|Prime Minister]] [[Lee Hsien Loong]] convenes a two-day special Parliamentary session to debate the accusations of abuse of power made by his siblings in the [[38 Oxley Road]] dispute.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/lee-family-feud-mps-call-independent-inquiry-abuse-power-allegations-141913743.html|title=Lee family feud: MPs call for independent inquiry on abuse of power allegations|last=Yong|first=Nicholas|date=3 July 2017|work=Yahoo News Singapore|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812065102/https://sg.news.yahoo.com/lee-family-feud-mps-call-independent-inquiry-abuse-power-allegations-141913743.html|archive-date=12 August 2017|url-status=live|language=en-SG|access-date=12 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> At the end of the debate, no evidence of abuse of power was found.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://in.reuters.com/article/singapore-politics-idINKBN19P0KF|title=Singapore's PM says parliament finds no evidence of abuse of power...|date=2017-07-04|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-04-06|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190125020442/https://in.reuters.com/article/singapore-politics-idINKBN19P0KF|archive-date=2019-01-25|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* 10 July \u2013 \n**PayNow comes into operation.<ref name=\"PayNow\"/>\n**The [[Sungei Road]] flea market is closed for good.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sungei Road Thieves' Market to shut for good on July 10 |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/sungei-road-thieves-market-close-good-july-10 |publisher=Todayonline |date=14 February 2017 |accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref>\n* 13 July \u2013 [[CapitaLand]] unveils a 280m tower that replaces the Golden Shoe Car Park. It started construction in 2018, later known as CapitaSpring. The building, which will incorporate a park at Market Street, will be completed by 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/182b-tower-to-replace-golden-shoe-car-park|title=$1.82b tower to replace Golden Shoe Car Park|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstimes.com.sg/companies-markets/market-street-to-get-park-footpaths-from-golden-shoe-car-park-redevelopment|title=Market Street to get park, footpaths from Golden Shoe Car Park redevelopment: Lawrence Wong|website=The Business Times|language=en|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tnp.sg/news/business/tower-going-old-golden-shoe-car-park-named-capitaspring|title=Tower going up at old Golden Shoe Car Park named CapitaSpring|website=The New Paper|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref>\n* 14 July \u2013 A new viaduct adjacent to the slip road from Upper Changi Road East to [[Pan Island Expressway|PIE]] collapses during casting of deck, killing one construction worker and injuring 10 others.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/structure-highway-construction-collapses-near-pie-leaving-1-dead-10-injured-002811390.html|title=Structure on highway under construction collapses near PIE, leaving 1 dead, 10 injured|date=14 July 2017|work=Yahoo News Singapore|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812063745/https://sg.news.yahoo.com/structure-highway-construction-collapses-near-pie-leaving-1-dead-10-injured-002811390.html|archive-date=12 August 2017|url-status=live|language=en-SG|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/uncompleted-viaduct-near-pie-collapses-1-dead-10-injured-9030432|title=Uncompleted viaduct near PIE collapses; 1 dead, 10 injured|date=14 July 2017|work=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021111950/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/uncompleted-viaduct-near-pie-collapses-1-dead-10-injured-9030432|archive-date=21 October 2017|url-status=live|language=en-GB|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* 17 July \u2013 The Pioneer Polyclinic opens, the first polyclinic to be built in more than 10 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/new-polyclinic-opens-in-jurong-west|title=New polyclinic opens in Jurong West |publisher=The Straits Times|date=27 July 2017|accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref>\n* 18 July \u2013 [[Tengah Air Base]] will be expanded to accommodate the relocation of [[Paya Lebar Air Base]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/tengah-air-base-to-be-expanded-more-than-80000-graves-exhumed-four-farms-to-be|title=Tengah Air Base to be expanded; more than 80,000 graves exhumed, 4 farms to be acquired|date=18 July 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=4 May 2019|language=en-SG}}</ref>\n* 22 July \u2013 Comic writer [[Sonny Liew]] wins 3 [[Eisner Award]]s for [[The Art of Charlie Chan Hock Chye]],<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Ho |first1=Olivia |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/graphic-novelist-sonny-liew-becomes-first-singaporean-to-win-eisner-award |title=Graphic novelist Sonny Liew is first Singaporean to win Eisner award, bagging 3 comics Oscars |website=The Straits Times |access-date=6 May 2019 |date=22 July 2017}}</ref> 2 years after the [[National Arts Council, Singapore|National Arts Council]] (NAC) withdrew funding for his book.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/national-arts-council-revokes-grant-for-graphic-novel-Sonny-Liew |title=NAC withdraws grant for graphic novel publisher due to \"sensitive content\" |website=Today |date=29 May 2015 |access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Charissa |url=https: