plan for Jurong Lake District is released by the [[Urban Redevelopment Authority]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/new-homes-jobs-lifestyle-in-jurong-lake-district|title=New homes, jobs, lifestyle in Jurong Lake District|date=31 August 2017|work=The Straits Times|url-status=live|language=en|access-date=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n**[[Mediacorp]] announced that it will acquire [[Singapore Press Holdings]]'s (SPH) stakes in Mediacorp TV (at 20 percent) and Mediacorp Press (at 40 percent) for [[S$]]18 million, which SPH will divest. This comes after Mediacorp announced that it will stop publishing the [[Today\u00a0(Singapore newspaper)|Today]] paper and go fully digital. In addition, Mediacorp will stop publishing any soft copy or digital format of Today that is similar to a hardcopy newspaper for five years.<ref>{{cite web |title=SPH to divest stakes in Mediacorp entities |url=https://sph.com.sg/media_releases/3283 |website=SPH |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mediacorp buys SPH\u2019s minority shareholdings of its entertainment television and newspaper businesses |url=https://www.mediacorp.sg/en/corporate/mediacorp-in-the-news/media-releases/mediacorp-buys-sph-s-minority-shareholdings-of-its-entertainment-9157914 |website=Mediacorp |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=TODAY moves to a fully digital future |url=https://www.mediacorp.sg/en/mediacorp-in-the-news/media-releases/today-moves-to-a-fully-digital-future-9157934 |website=Mediacorp |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Yahya |first1=Yasmine |title=SPH to divest stakes in Mediacorp TV and Press while Today newspaper will cease print edition and go fully digital |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/companies-markets/sph-to-divest-stakes-in-mediacorp-tv-and-press-while-today-newspaper-will |website=The Straits Times |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Today\">{{cite web |last1=Mokhtar |first1=Faris |title=TODAY goes fully digital from Oct, to end print edition after 17-year run |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/today-go-full-digital-oct-end-print-edition-after-17-year-run |website=Today |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=TODAY newspaper to cease print edition, go fully digital |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/today-newspaper-to-cease-print-edition-go-fully-digital-9157872 |website=Channel NewsAsia |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref> The acquisition is completed on 29 September.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Woo |first1=Jacqueline |title=SPH completes sale of Mediacorp stakes |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/companies-markets/sph-completes-sale-of-mediacorp-stakes |website=The Straits Times |date=30 September 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n* 29 August \u2013 The [[Land Transport Authority]] announced the scrapping of the [[Singapore Underground Road System]]. This move frees up land reserved for the project.<ref>{{cite web |title=Singapore scraps underground road network plans for city; land owners to have greater flexibility in land use |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/singapore-scraps-underground-road-network-plans |website=The Straits Times |date=29 August 2017 |accessdate=27 June 2019}}</ref>\n* 31 August \u2013\n**[[Tony Tan]] steps down from Presidency.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/president-tony-tan-leaves-office-today|title=President Tony Tan leaves office today|last=Toh|first=Elgin|date=31 August 2017|work=The Straits Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713012406/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/president-tony-tan-leaves-office-today|archive-date=13 July 2018|url-status=live|language=en|access-date=6 April 2019|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Chairman of the [[Powers of the President of Singapore|Council of Presidential