s/singapore/tan-chuan-jin-becomes-singapore-s-10th-speaker-of-parliament-9204766|title=Tan Chuan-Jin becomes Singapore\u2019s 10th Speaker of Parliament|date=11 September 2017|work=CNA|access-date=25 July 2019|language=en-SG}}</ref>\n**A new crossover track will be built at [[Canberra MRT station]] to lessen the impact of train service disruptions should they happen.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Chong |first1=Clara |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/canberra-mrt-station-to-have-crossover-track-to-minimise-train-service-disruptions |title=Canberra MRT station to have crossover track to minimise train service disruptions |website=The Straits Times |access-date=1 November 2019 |date=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n**[[2017 Singaporean presidential election|2017 Presidential Election]]: former [[Speaker of Parliament (Singapore)|Speaker]] [[Halimah Yacob]] is announced by the Presidential Elections Commission as the only candidate issued with both the certificate of eligibility and community certificate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/halimah-yacob-only-one-to-get-eligibility-certificate-set-to-be-singapores-next-president|title=Halimah Yacob only one to get eligibility certificate, set to be Singapore's next President|last=Yong|first=Charissa|date=11 September 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=14 September 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n* 13 September \u2013 \n** Two ships collide near Singapore waters, causing two casualties and seven injured, with another three missing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/two-ships-collide-in-singapore-waters-five-crew-members-missing|title=Two ships collide in Singapore waters; 7 injured, 2 dead, 3 missing|last=Lai|first=Linette|date=14 September 2017|work=The Straits Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190125020540/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/two-ships-collide-in-singapore-waters-five-crew-members-missing|archive-date=25 January 2019|url-status=live|last2=Seow|fi