 system for permanent residency applications, first announced on 2 November.<ref>{{cite web |title=ICA to roll out electronic system for permanent residency applications |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/ica-to-roll-out-electronic-system-for-permanent-residency-9367982 |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=31 December 2019 |date=2 November 2017}}</ref>\n* 19 December \u2013 [[Singapore Power]] announced that the North-South, East-West and Jurong Island Cable Tunnels will progressively start operations from end-2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-s-deepest-cable-tunnel-system-to-transmit-electricity-9510330|title=Singapore's deepest cable tunnel system to transmit electricity from end-2018|date=19 December 2017|work=CNA|access-date=6 June 2019}}</ref>\n* 20 December \u2013 Parking.sg is extended to those using motorcycles and heavy vehicles, making it available for all vehicle users at all car parks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/parking-sg-app-to-be-available-for-motorcycles-heavy-vehicles-9509384 |title=Parking.sg app to be available for motorcycles, heavy vehicles from Dec 20 |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=9 November 2019 |date=19 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 22 December \u2013 [[Keppel Corporation|Keppel O&M]] agrees to pay up to US$422m in fines for a bribery case to US, Brazilian and Singapore authorities in a plea deal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/companies-markets/keppel-om-to-pay-us422m-in-fines-to-settle-bribery-probe|title=Keppel O&M to pay US$422m in fines to settle bribery probe|date=23 December 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=24 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180924145628/https://www.straitstimes.com/business/companies-markets/keppel-om-to-pay-us422m-in-fines-to-settle-bribery-probe|archive-date=24 September 2018|url-status=live|language=en|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n*16 January \u2013 [[Amin Nasir]], football player (b. 1968).\n*19 January \u2013 Juanita Melson, DJ and MRT announcer (b. 1944).<ref>{{cite web |title=Former voice of MRT announcements Juanita Melson dies |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/former-voice-of-mrt-announcements-juanita-melson-dies |publisher=The Straits Times |date=23 January 2017 |accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref>\n*26 January \u2013 Tan See Lai, educator, newscaster (b. 1934).<ref>{{cite web |title=Dozens pay respects to pioneer educator, newscaster Tan See Lai |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/dozens-pay-respects-to-pioneer-educator-newscaster-tan-see-lai-7561898 |publisher=The Straits Times |date=29 January 2017 |accessdate=22 July 2019}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 [[Fong Swee Suan]], trade unionist (b. 1931).<ref>{{cite web |title=Former leftist trade unionist Fong Swee Suan dies, aged 85 |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/former-leftist-trade-unionist-fong-swee-suan-dies-aged-85 |publisher=The Straits Times |date=5 February 2017 |accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Fong Swee Suan |url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/infopedia/articles/SIP_2013-07-29_173512.html |publisher=NLB |accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref>\n*27 February \u2013 [[Sin Kek Tong]], opposition veteran, founder of [[Singapore People's Party]] (b. 1944).<ref>{{cite web |title=Opposition veteran and Singapore People's Party founder Sin Kek Tong dies |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/opposition-veteran-and-singapore-peoples-party-founder-sin-kek-tong-dies |publisher=The Straits Times |date=1 March 2017 |accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref>\n*17 April \u2013 [[Othman Wok]], politician and ambassador (b. 1924).<ref>{{cite web |title=Othman Wok, member of independent Singapore's first Cabinet, dies aged 92 |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/othman-wok-member-of-independent-singapores-first-cabinet-dies-aged-92 |publisher=The Straits Times |date=17 April 2017 |accessdate=22 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Othman Wok |url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/infopedia/articles/SIP_995_2009-07-01.html |publisher=NLB |accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref>\n*22 April \u2013 [[Rufino Soliano]], musician (b. 1932).<ref>{{cite web |title=Rufino Soliano |url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/infopedia/articles/SIP_2015-03-17_093353.html |publisher=NLB |accessdate=7 August 2019}}</ref>\n*11 July - [[Maurice Baker (Singapore)|Maurice Baker]], academic, diplomat (b. 1920).<ref>{{cite web |title=Maurice Baker |url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/infopedia/articles/SIP_1538_2009-09-10.html |website=NLB |accessdate=29 October 2019}}</ref>\n*7 September \u2013 [[Duncan Watt]], writer, newscaster (b. 1942).<ref>{{cite web |title=Writer and former newscaster Duncan Watt dies, aged 74 |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/writer-and-former-newscaster-duncan-watt-has-died |publisher=The Straits Times |date=7 September 2017 |accessdate=22 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2017]]\n*[[History of Singapore]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Years in Singapore}}\n{{Asia topic|2017 in}}\n\n[[Category:2017 in Singapore| ]]\n[[Category:2017 in Southeast Asia|Singapore]]\n[[Category:2010s in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Years of the 21st century in Singapore]]\n[[Category:2017 by country|Singapore]]\n", "name_user": "TheGreatSG'rean", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSeptember", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2017_in_Singapore"}
